The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Saturday, January 31, 2004 				Metro Recommends
				 																The Book				 																																	(Claude  Markovits) Delving into the life and afterlife of the Mahatma,  the author stresses the paradoxical modernity of Gandhis  anti-modernism. From the creation of Gandhi to his role in  the public sphere, the book shows how his various contributions  make him an enduring figure  The Show				 																																	(Gyan  Manch, February 6, 6.30 pm) The 90-minute dance theatre based  on the story of Cinderella features Katia Marlot from Paris,  Tilak and Swapna Sen with puppetry, Dipanwita Roy with Odissi  and others  The exhibition				 																																	(Academy  of Fine Arts, February 3 to 12, 3 pm to 8 pm) The annual art  exhibition features the works of some of the citys best known  artists, including Rabin Mondal, Isha Mohammad, Jogen Chowdhury  and Prakash Karmakar (painting above)  The album				 																																	(Various)  Fifty-five songs packed into four cassettes capture the essence  of the swingin seventies, when the great R.D. Burman was  creating magic. A must-buy, if only to hear Chadti jawani  and Haye re haye tera ghungta, original and un-remixed! 
